  <bioghist id="aspace_8cdb510b86ff66fb4b802ff1f2e81dd0">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Teacher, author, lecturer, composer.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_f698c86ba92eb0d072b1d718dcb2ce1c">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Incoming letters concerning Kenney's writings; religious, ethical, and scientific questions; Cornell University alumni affairs; and personal and family matters. Also, manuscript and published copies of Kenney's autobiographical writings, essays, poems, and musical compositions; photographs; newspaper clippings, broadsides, pamphlets, programs, and other printed items pertaining to his literary career, Cornell, the Washington Secular Society, women's suffrage, national politics, and various public issues.</p>  </scopecontent>
